01/05/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Parliament on Monday (April 30th) approved new ministerial appointments prompted by the sudden resignation of Besnik Mustafaj as foreign minister.
Lulzim Basha is taking his post, while Sokol Olldashi takes over Basha's old job as transport and telecommunications minister.
In other news Monday, the Central Electoral Commission announced that local elections must be repeated in 20 local districts on Sunday, due to irregularities in elections on February 18th.
Parties were urged to immediately post the names of their candidates in these races.
(Top-Channel, Kohajone - 01/05/07;
Balkanweb, VOA, 24-ore - 30/04/07)
